title: Duplicate ESM import alias
body:

Repo for reproduction: https://github.com/arackaf/booklist/tree/feature/rollup2 (that branch specifically).

Drop down into the react-redux folder.  

npm i (from there!)
npm run rollup

If you go into `public/module/chunk5.js` you should see this

```javascript
import { rootReducer, thunkMiddleware, store, getNewReducer } from './chunk4.js';
import { applyMiddleware, createStore, combineReducers, connect, Provider } from './chunk2.js';
import { SET_IS_TOUCH, SET_DESKTOP, SET_MOBILE, REQUEST_DESKTOP, REQUEST_MOBILE, SET_MODULE, SET_LOGGED_IN, SET_PUBLIC_INFO, LOAD_SUBJECTS, LOAD_SUBJECTS_RESULTS, LOAD_COLORS, SAVE_SUBJECT_RESULTS, SUBJECT_DELETED, _propTypes as propTypes } from './chunk3.js';
import { ajaxUtil, React as react, react_3, react_4, require$$4 as objectAssign, commonjsGlobal, commonjsRequire, unwrapExports, createCommonjsModule } from './chunk1.js';
import { reactDom_2, reactDom_1 } from './chunk6.js';
import { _react as react } from './chunk7.js';
```

note the duplicate import aliases named "react." (lines 4 and 6)  Needless to say this errors out at runtime.

This is using Rollup `0.55.5`, though of course everything is listed in the package.json file in THIS directory, (react-redux)
